      "bezeichnung": "Embedded Software Engineering 2",
      "planinhalt": "<p><strong>Beurteilung von Komplexit&auml;t und Performance</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Komplexit&auml;tstheorie</li>\n<li>Performance Profiling</li>\n<li>C vs. C++</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Effective C++ for Embedded Systems</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Avoiding code and data bloat</li>\n<li>Interface-based programming (runtime, link-time and compile-time polymorphism)</li>\n<li>ROMability</li>\n<li>Memory-mapped I/O, e.g. with templates</li>\n<li>Dynamic memory management</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Securing Embedded Systems using Crypto Engines</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Random Number Generators (Pseudo RNG, Cryptographically Secure PRNG, True RNG)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Effiziente Cyclic Redundancy Checks (CRC)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Bootloader</strong></p>\n<p>&Auml;nderungen vorbehalten</p>",
